==Chinese==

===Etymology===
From "large tangerine" [[柑]] + "orange" [[橘]].

===Pronunciation===
*Mandarin
**Pinyin: gān jú
*Cantonese
**Jyutping: gam1 gwat1

===Noun===
'''[[柑]][[橘]]''' ''simplified and traditional''

# the Cantonese name for [[kumquat]].

====Alternative forms====
*[[金橘]] (the original name for kumquat, and that used in standard Chinese, is ''jīnjú'', literally "golden orange," also pronounced ''gam1 gwat1'' in Cantonese)

In Mandarin Chinese it is pronounced ''gān jú'', literally "large tangerine orange."  The original name of this fruit in standard (Mandarin) Chinese, however, is 

